===Etymology===
From {{etyl|pt|en}} or {{etyl|es|en}} {{m|pt|búfalo||buffalo}} from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{m|la|būfalus}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|būbalus}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|βούβαλος||antelope, wild ox}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈbʌf.əl.əʊ/|lang=en}}
** {{audio|en-uk-Buffalo.ogg|Audio (UK)|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|bŭf'ə-lō}}, {{IPA|/ˈbʌf.ə.loʊ/|lang=en}}
** {{audio|en-us-buffalo.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|buffaloes|buffalos|buffalo}}

# Any of the Old World mammals of the family [[Bovidae]], such as the [[Cape buffalo]], {{taxlink|Syncerus caffer|species|noshow=1}}, or the [[water buffalo]] {{taxlink|Buabalus bubalis|species|noshow=1}}.
# A related North American animal, the [[American bison]], ''[[Bison bison]]''.
# A buffalo robe.
# The [[buffalo fish]].

